==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intumesce
<hw>In`tu*mesce"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Intumesced</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Intumescing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>intumescere</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>tumescere</ets>
to swell up, incho. fr. <ets>tumere</ets> to swell. See
<er>Tumid</er>.]</ety> <def>To enlarge or expand with heat; to swell;
specifically, to swell up or bubble up under the action of heat, as
before the blowpipe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In a higher heat, it <qex>intumesces</qex>, and melts into a
yellowish black mass.</q> <rj><qau>Kirwan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intumescence</ent>⟦br⟧
